HEADWORD: maltese cross
<hw>maltese cross</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A Eurasian
garden perennial (<spn>Lychins chalcedonica</spn>) having scarlet
flowers in dense terminal heads.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> scarlet lychnis, <spn>Lychins
chalcedonica</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A cross with triangular or arrow-shaped arms and the
points toward the center. See illustration under
<er>cross</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Maltese dog</ent>⟦br⟧
